<br />

<br />
SM I/II was most valuable to keep a pet/buffed pet while you Pet Canni.  It also allowed the ability to travel invis with a pet AS LONG AS YOU STOPPED AND UNSPENDED BEFORE YOU ZONED.  
<br />

<br />
Once Pet Canni was no more, the biggest use of SM was gone.   Groups never wanted to wait for you to competely buff a single pet, let along two so I almost never used SM after I got it.  Especailly after pets could zone.  With SM III, I can have a pet always and won't dissappear by succoring, accidently zoning, or even camping out. 
<br />

<br />
Typically, I get my best tank {Earth Pet} and equip/buff him to the max and suspend/unspend as I travel.  Once I am in the zone, I supend my pet and use the best pet for what we are doing.  With SM III, the only time I should lose my pet is if I die.  I plan to run around with an Earth Pet equipped with a slowing/snaring weapon for those OMG over pulls.  
<br />

<br />
I think SM III adds a lot of value back to SM.<br />_________________<br />Dabrighter Blazemeister
